5. Spectrophotometry (UV-Vis, AAS, ICP-AES, ICP-MS)
5.1 UV-Visible Spectrophotometry
Beer-Lambert Law – Foundation of Spectrophotometry
A = e × b × c OR A = log(In/I) = -log(T)
Where:
A = absorbance (dimensionless; log scale)
e = molar absorptivity (L/mol·cm); characteristic for each compound at each wavelength
b = path length of light through sample (cm; typically 1 cm cuvette)
c = concentration (mol/L or mg/L with appropriate e)
T = transmittance = I/In; %T = T × 100
Linear range: A = 0.1–1.0 for best accuracy; dilute if A > 1.0
Limitations: only applies to dilute solutions, monochromatic light, no scattering, no fluorescence
